Rob Corddry https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rob_Corddry 0 Robert William Corddry (born February 4, 1971) is an American actor and comedian. He is known for his work as a correspondent on The Daily Show with Jon Stewart (2002–2006) and for his starring role in the film Hot Tub Time Machine. He is the creator and star of the Adult Swim series Childrens Hospital and has been awarded four Primetime Emmy Awards. He currently co-stars in the HBO series Ballers.
